Pre-heat your oven to 220 degrees and put the @bamboo skewers{10} in a #bowl{} of water to soak them.

> This will prevent them burning too much in the oven!

Chop the @red potato{2} into wedges about the length and width of your index finger (no need to peel!). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{125%g} and leave to the side.

Put your potato wedges on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over enough @olive oil{} to just coat them. Sprinkle over a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and give the tray a shake, until your wedges get a good coating of oil and seasoning. Put on the top shelf of your oven to roast for ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn your wedges after ~{12%minutes}.

Remove the cores from the @red pepper{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks) and @yellow pepper{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks) and chop them into 2cm chunks. Cut the @red onion{1%large}(cut in half through the root, peeled and chopped into six pieces) and separate your onion layers.

Chop the @British honey mustard sausages{8}(cut into bite-sized chunks) into bite-sized chunks (about 2cm wide). Put your veggies and sausage into a large bowl and pour over half the @BBQ sauce{8%tbsp}. Mix together carefully with your hands.

Thread your veggie and sausage pieces onto your skewers in the following order: sausage - pepper - a couple of onion pieces and so on.

> You should make eight skewers in total but we've given you a couple extra in case you have any leftovers!

> It's great to have kids helping in the kitchen and getting used to cooking, but just make sure everyone washes their hands after handling raw meat!

Put your sausage skewers on a lightly oiled baking tray (or on some baking paper on a baking tray if you have some). Move your wedges to the middle shelf and pop your skewers on the top shelf. Cook for ~{20-25%minutes} until crispy and cooked through.

Now it's time to make the dressing. Wash up the #large bowl{} you used for your veggies and sausage. Squeeze the @lemon{1}(juiced) juice into the bowl and then add in the @wholegrain mustard{1%tsp}, the @honey{1%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and the @extra virgin olive oil{3%tbsp}. Whisk together with a #fork{}.

Next prepare the avocado. Cut into the @avocado{1} lengthways until you reach the stone. Turn the knife around the stone to cut it in two then remove the stone. While the avocado is still in its skin, carefully cut small squares into the flesh. Use a #spoon{} to scoop the flesh out into the bowl with your dressing. Add the @baby leaf salad{2%handfuls} and toss well.

Give your kitchen a quick tidy and get your washing up done!

When your sausage skewers are cooked, remove from your oven and cover with #tinfoil{}. Pre-heat your #grill{} to high. Sprinkle your cheese over your potato wedges and pop under your grill for ~{3-5%minutes}, or until your cheese has melted and is bubbling.

Serve your skewers with your cheesy wedges and lemony salad on the side, along with a dollop of leftover BBQ sauce. Enjoy!